statement:
Let \( D \) be a point inside acute triangle \( ABC \) such that
\[ \angle ADB = \angle ACB + \frac{\pi}{2} \quad\text{and}\quad AC \cdot BD = AD \cdot BC. \]
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(a)] Calculate the ratio \( \frac{AB \cdot CD}{AC \cdot BD} \).
\item[(b)] Prove that the tangents at \( C \) to the circumcircles of triangles \( ACD \) and \( BCD \) are perpendicular.
\end{enumerate}
